# Original PsyQ cc1 binary (proprietary — gitignored, never committed).
# RESTORED 2026-05-29 as a self-disproof tool: an agent that suspects a
# "compiler divergence" can run BOTH compilers and SEE that cc1psx does not
# beat decompals (it matches, or is worse — see docs/diagnostics/
# compiler_parity.txt and memory/rules/compiler-patch-low-roi.md). The
# compiler is NOT the variable; a non-match is a C-source problem. Running
# cc1psx is no longer blocked (the cc1psx_guard hook was removed).
#
# Run it (drop-in cc1, reads preprocessed C on stdin, writes asm on stdout):
#   tools/cc1psx_wrapper.sh <cc1-flags> < foo.i    # via dosemu2
# Compare:  diff <(cc1 ... foo.i) <(tools/cc1psx_wrapper.sh ... < foo.i)
#
# If the binary is missing, retrieve it:
#   curl -L https://archive.org/download/psyq-sdk/PSYQ_SDK.zip -o /tmp/sdk.zip
#   python3 -c "import zipfile;zipfile.ZipFile('/tmp/sdk.zip').extract('psyq/psyq/CC1PSX.EXE','/tmp')"
#   cp /tmp/psyq/psyq/CC1PSX.EXE tools/cc1psx.exe
tools/cc1psx.exe

